item.title: COVID-19 Analysis
item.description: Introduction Coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19) is a contagious respiratory and vascular disease. Since its outbreak in December 2019 from Wuhan, China, it has presented the world with many political, scientific and public health challenges. Some researchers identified some important nutritional considerations for the prevention and management of COVID-19 diseases, including the role of select micronutri- ents (vitamins and minerals), phytochemicals and probiotics in conferring protection against both viral infection and pathogenicity.
